Progressive Sisters’ Network (PSN), an All Progressives Congress (APC) support group focused on women’s issues, has honoured Bola Tinubu with a human development award. Tinubu, standard-bearer of the APC, received the award on Sunday, at an event organised by the group in Abuja. The event tagged: ‘Meet the Mentor’, was hosted by Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives. Rinsola Abiola, the coordinator of the group, said Tinubu is the first recipient of an award from the organisation. See photos from the event below:               